<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Ok, well, I'm a lvl 30 warrior. And the best i have learned really is on who and what you are fighting... If you are about to fight, say an ogre, or a hill giant something that is slower, you want duel weild, fast hits than they are giving you. Yes, you will lack in over all damage, but, they will be hitting you twice as slow. However, a really effective 1HS weapon is the wurmslayer, great stats for the damage you put out. That is, if you can afford one. 2HS weapons are great on things that will smack you around a lot. Like Orcs, Gnolls, stuff like that, you deliver a lot more damage to them and they wear themselves out easier when you are hitting them for so much. I myself love duel weild, sporting a Wurmslayer in Right hand, and a Centrum Blade in off hand... Makes it easy but yellow health bar drains fast with that wurmslayer. Hope this helped!<p>

<br>
Rhanhill Quakes</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
