<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=stormwindsong&Board=warrior&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Stormwind (stormwindsong) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I got into a debate just yesterday with a lvl 52 warrior that was using dual wield. We did a mock duel to test both opinions. Here is what we figured out. My ogre is lvl 20. Until you hit about lvl 40, there are 2H weapons that will be able to put out more damage. He told me that after lvl 40, your dual wield really takes off. At lvl 52, with the weapons he was using, which weren't the best, he was averaging about 980 points of damage a minute. At lvl 20, my ogre was doing a max of 600 per minute. From all that i can tell, lvl 40 is the average line that separates 1H and 2H. Untill then, he told me it was best to stick with 2H if you want the most damage. You won't be hitting as fast, but the average damage is better. Even at lvl 52, his highest hit on me was 38, average was 22. At lvl 20, my highest was 63, average was 55. <p>

When it comes down to it, it is a matter of personal taste. I've tried both. With my str, i find using my Executioner's Axe to be the most effective one for me. It will depend a lot on Lvl, Str and the weapons you are using. <p>

Rumman SoulSteeler<br>
Ogre Warrior of 20 seasons<br>
E'ci Server</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
