<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=arrion&Board=warrior&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=Session&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Arrion (arrion) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I am now a level 42 warrior and have used both 1hs and 2hs quite often.  I took someone's excellent advice and made sure that I kept both skills maxxed out as I leveled.  As soon as I hit the skill cap for one, I would switch to the other.  While in the mid-20's until lvl 37 , I was using an Exe axe for 2hs and a Runed Falchion/BBK combo for 1hs.  Obviously, I was doing much greater damage with the Exe Axe.  However, after saving my money, I was able to acquire a Wurmslayer and SSOY for dual wield.  <br>
  For those of you not familiar with the WS, it is AC 5 +5str 25 40 1hs but weighs 15.0 (meaning it will wear on your stamina).  This is an incredible weapon and I may not ever go back to 2hs.  The WS is like a one-handed Exe Axe with a permanent haste proc that boots AC and str also.  My average damage is dbl 57's with crits up to 157, and I routinely hit normally for 80-95.  I agree with the previous post.  2hs is probably preferred to lvl 35-40, but after that 1hs is better.  Just keep skills maxxed and you will have the option of switching between them- let one go and you will have to live with your choice.<p>

Arrion Robespierre<br>
42 Warrior <br>
Bertoxx/ Storm Wolf Guild</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
